ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Let me check a few more things to complete my review:\n1. The Makefil
e changes\n2. The run-e2e.sh changes\n3. Check if there\'s a BDD feature file fo
r IM\n4. Check the pubspec.yaml changes for mobile\n5. Check if there are any un
it tests for IM service or gateway\n6. The api.md for API design standards\n\nI 
also need to look at some potential issues I\'ve spotted so far:\n- ImModule cre
ates its own REDIS_CLIENT provider, but MatchingModule also creates one. This co
uld mean two Redis connections.\n- ImGateway.handleConnection joins `user:${payl
oad.sub}` but handleDisconnect leaves it. However, Socket.io automatically clean
s up rooms on disconnect, so this is redundant but harmless.\n- ImGateway.emitCo
nversationUpdated takes senderId and receiverId, but in handleSendMessage it pas
ses userId and otherId. The otherId could be null.\n- In ImService.sendMessage, 
the `client_message_id` uniqueness check: if dto.client_message_id is null, it g
enerates uuidv7(), but then the duplicate check requires `dto.client_message_id`
to be truthy.\n- The `getMessages` method returns `next_cursor` as `String(messa
ges[0].sequence_id)` but messages are reversed, so messages[0] is actually the o
ldest message in the returned set, not the newest. This means the next cursor wo
uld be incorrect for "load more" pagination.\n- In chat_page.dart, `_sendMessage
` uses `uuid.v4()` for clientMessageId but the event defaults type to \'text\'. 
However, looking at ImSendMessage event, the type parameter defaults to \'text\'
in the event class, but chat_page doesn\'t pass it explicitly. That\'s fine sinc
e it has a default.\n- In ImBloc._onMessageReceived, it checks if `event.message
.conversationId != _currentConversationId` and returns early. But what if the me
ssage is from the current conversation but the sender is the current user? It sh
ould still update (for multi-device sync).\n- In ImBloc._onReadReceipt, it only 
marks one message as read (the one matching lastReadMessageId), but PRD says "Bo
b\'s unread count should be reset to 0" - which happens on the backend. But for 
frontend, it should probably mark all messages up to that point as read, not jus
t the one matching exactly.\n- The Maestro E2E flow `send_message.yaml` has `ass
ertVisible: "你好"` but the chat bubble content might not be directly visible as
