StepBegin(n=12)
ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think="Let me read the im.yaml API contract to verify it's consistent with t
he implementation, and also check one of the BDD step definition files for IM to
see if they were properly set up. I also want to check if the generated types in
shared-types are properly exported.\n\nI also want to check if there are any iss
ues with the way `ImBloc` is disposed - specifically in `app.dart`, the `ImBloc`
is created via `getIt<ImBloc>()` for each chat page. Since `ImBloc` is registere
d as `registerFactory`, a new instance is created each time. But `ImBloc.close()
` disconnects the socket. When the user navigates away from chat page, the bloc 
is disposed and socket is disconnected. But the `MatchListPage` might need the s
ocket connection alive for `conversation:updated` events. Let me check how `Matc
hListPage` handles this.\n\nActually, looking at `app.dart`:\n```dart\nGoRoute(\
n  path: '/chat',\n  builder: (context, state) {\n    final extra = state.extra 
as Map<String, dynamic>? ?? {};\n    return BlocProvider(\n      create: (_) => 
getIt<ImBloc>(),\n      child: ChatPage(...),\n    );\n  },\n),\n```\n\nThe `ImB
loc` is created fresh for each ChatPage. When the page is popped, the BlocProvid
er disposes the bloc, which calls `close()`, which disconnects the socket. This 
means:\n1. User opens chat -> socket connects\n2. User goes back to match list -
> socket disconnects\n3. User receives a push notification or opens another chat
-> socket reconnects\n\nThis is inefficient. More importantly, the `MatchListPag
e` doesn't have access to the `ImBloc` or socket connection, so it can't receive
`conversation:updated` events to refresh the conversation list in real-time. The
`conversation:updated` event handler in `ImBloc._onConversationUpdated` is empty
anyway, but the architectural gap is there.\n\nHowever, the PRD doesn't explicit
ly require real-time conversation list updates. The match list page fetches conv
ersations on init. So this is more of a design issue than a blocking bug.\n\nBut
there's another issue: when the user is in a chat and receives a message, the so
cket client auto-marks it as read. When the user navigates back to the match lis
t, the socket disconnects. If they then open the same conversation again, a new 
socket connection is established. This is functional but not optimal.\n\nA more 
serious issue: what if the user is on the MatchListPage and a new message arrive
s? They won't get a real-time unread count update. But again, the PRD doesn't ex
plicitly require this for MVP.\n\nLet me check the BDD step definitions for IM t
o see if they're implemented or just stubs.",
    encrypted=None
)
