ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the PR. Let me summarize 
the key findings:\n\n## Critical Issues (Blocking)\n\n1. **BDD Step Definitions 
for IM are stubs** - The IM BDD step definition files (`im_*.steps.js`) only imp
ort `commonSteps` and use `autoBindSteps`. The `commonSteps` doesn\'t define IM-
specific steps like "Alice and Bob are both online and connected via Socket.io" 
or "Alice sends \'在吗？\'". These BDD tests will fail because the steps are und
efined. This violates `testing.md` which says BDD tests must cover full user sto
ries.\n\nWait, actually `jest-cucumber`\'s `autoBindSteps` might not fail if ste
ps are undefined - it might just skip them or fail. Either way, the BDD tests fo
r IM are not actually implemented. However, looking at the common.js file, I see
that it DOES define some IM-related steps (lines 159-210). So `autoBindSteps(fea
ture, [commonSteps])` will actually bind the steps from common.js that match the
feature file!\n\nLet me re-check. The `common.js` exports a function that takes 
`{ given, when, then, and }` and registers step definitions. `autoBindSteps` sca
ns the feature file and tries to match steps with registered definitions. Since 
`common.js` does define IM steps, the BDD tests might actually work!\n\nBut wait
- the steps in `common.js` are all empty (`() => {}`). They don\'t actually impl
ement any test logic. So the BDD tests will "pass" but they don\'t actually test
anything. This is a known issue with the existing codebase pattern - the BDD tes
ts are acceptance-level stubs.\n\nLooking at the testing.md: "BDD 测试验证的是业
务行为". Empty step definitions don\'t validate business behavior. But this seem
s to be the existing pattern in the project. The matching service spec changes a
dded unit tests, but BDD remains stub-based.\n\nHmm, but the task says I should 
review this PR against project standards. The BDD step definitions for IM were a
dded in this PR (they didn\'t exist before). If they\'re just stubs, that\'s not
great. But they follow the same pattern as the existing common.js. This might be
a Minor issue rather than Blocking.\n\nActually, I should focus on what this PR 
specifically changed and whether those changes meet standards.\n\n## Major Issue
s\n\n1. **Push Service not integrated in IM module** - The PRD (v1-mvp.md) expli
citly says: "离线用户通过极光推送/Firebase 触发新消息提醒". The BDD feature `im_
real_time_message_delivery.feature` also says "a push notification should be tri
ggered for Bob" when Bob is offline. But `PushService` is not injected into `ImM
odule` and `ImGateway` never calls it. This is a functional gap.\n\n2. **No API 
unit tests for IM module** - The PR adds `im.service.ts`, `im.gateway.ts`, `im.c
ontroller.ts` but zero unit/integration tests. The `matching.service.spec.ts` wa
s updated (it existed before), but no new spec files were created for IM. The `t
esting.md` says "后端：NestJS 使用 Jest，覆盖率目标 >80%".\n\n3. **Missing Socke
t event contract YAML** - The `api.md` requires: "后端每新增一个 `server.emit()`
/ `socket.emit()` 事件，必须同时满足：`docs/api-contracts/<module>-events.yaml` 
中定义了该事件的 Schema". There is no `im-events.yaml` file. The events `message
:receive`, `message:ack`, `message:read_receipt`, `conversation:updated`, `messa
ge:error` are emitted but not documented in a YAML contract.\n\n4. **Maestro E2E
`send_message.yaml` assumes conversation exists without creating one** - The flo
w tries to tap on `conversation_item` (optional), then asserts `chat_back_button
` (optional), then unconditionally taps `chat_input_field` and sends a message. 
If no conversation exists (which is likely in a fresh E2E environment), the test
will fail on `chat_input_field`. The `view_conversation_list.yaml` handles empty
state properly, but `send_message.yaml` doesn\'t.\n\n5. **ImBloc read receipt ma
rks only one message as read** - In `_onReadReceipt`, only the message exactly m
atching `lastReadMessageId` is marked as \'read\'. The BDD says "all unread mess
ages from Alice should be marked as \'read\'" and "Alice should see the message 
status change to \'已读\' for the last message". For MVP, marking just the last 
one might be acceptable, but it would look weird if earlier messages still show 
as "sent".\n\nWait, let me re-read the BDD:\n```\ngiven(\'Bob has received 3 unr
ead messages from Alice\', () => {});\nthen(\'all unread messages from Alice sho
uld be marked as "read"\', () => {});\nthen(\'Alice should see the message statu
s change to "已读" for the last message\', () => {});\nthen(\'Bob\\\'s unread co
unt for this conversation should be reset to 0\', () => {});\n```\n\nThe common.
js step is empty, but the feature description says "all unread messages... shoul
d be marked as read". The current implementation only marks the one matching exa
ctly. This is a functional deviation.\n\nActually, looking at `chat_page.dart`, 
`showStatus` is only true for `isSelf && index == messages.length - 1`. So only 
the last message shows a status indicator anyway. Marking only the last message 
as \'read\' would visually look correct because only the last message shows stat
us. But from a data model perspective, it\'s incorrect.\n\n6. **ImService.getCon
versations raw SQL IN (?) with empty array** - If `conversationIds` is empty (wh
ich is checked with `if (conversationIds.length > 0)`), the query is skipped. Th
at\'s fine.\n\n7. **ImModule and MatchingModule both create separate Redis clien
ts** - This is a code smell but consistent with existing code. Not a blocking is
sue.\n\n## Minor Issues\n\n1. **ImBloc created per ChatPage and disconnected on 
pop** - Not optimal for real-time updates, but functional for MVP.\n2. **Widgetb
ook golden test for SwChatInputBar shows two identical instances** - The golden 
test renders two `SwChatInputBar(onSend: _)` instances that look identical. Not 
